  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Lac Salin takes their food seriously! The kitchen team spend a lot of time a effort sourcing their ingredients and where possible from the local region. They grow and make a lot of their own produce, so you can expect quality home made food.</p>
<p>Breakfast is the most important meal of the day and you wont be disappointed by the wide selection of both hot and cold items from the buffet table. </p>
<p>The evening meal is really when the chefs get creative. Each night you are served up five delicious courses. It all starts up at the buffest table with a large selection of starters to choose from. You can then pick from the menu the next few courses before heading back to the buffet to feast your eyes on deserts buffet and selection of cheeses, so make sure you leave room. As if that wasn't good enough, there's even live music two or three times a week during dinner!</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>One of the <a data-udi="umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393" href="/{localLink:umb://document/47c7f0773b104efb87f3357e7314f393}" title="The Dolomites Ski Area">Dolomites</a> best hotels, the Adler Spa Resort Dolomiti is the perfect choice for your next Italian ski holiday. Dating back to the 1800s, the property retains its charm whilst offering a luxurious alpine retreat for its guests. The team here will do all they can to make your stay memorable. The Seceda lift's only 200 metres away so you have easy access to the slopes and if you're not up for walking then you can also hop on the free resort bus.</p>
<h2>Soothing spa</h2>
<p>After a busy day skiing, make time to visit the state-of-the-art spa which has plenty of great facilities. Float around in the indoor pool or unwind in the steam rooms or newly renovated saunas. Soak up the mountain views in the outdoor heated pool and if you really want to treat yourself, book in for one of their award-winning treatments (payable locally). There's lots to keep the whole family entertained here - children can play board games, video games and even watch films at the AKI kids club. </p>
<h2>Food and drink</h2>
<p>The meals at the Adler are fantastic, a lot of effort goes into sourcing seasonal and regional ingredients to create a menu which includes hearty South Tyrolean Alpine dishes and Italian-Mediterranean cuisine. </p>
<p>Each morning you can fuel up for the day at the varied breakfast buffet which includes sweet and savoury options. When you return from a day on the slopes, head to the cocktail bar and a handcrafted cocktail or a glass of wine. There's live music a few times a week too. </p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Adler Spa Resort Dolomiti the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
